Description: Gold round and domed rosette made of a thin embossed sheet of metal, with a large irregular central hole and six U-shaped petals, either a bead or part of a clasp. The outer edge is partly shreded.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, From the denuded surface of the site or the neighbourhood ?
Curator's comments: "gold foil, floret" mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 110, pl. xli, 16. On the gold material from Tell Dafana, see ibid., p. 76 § 73-74.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 110, pl. xli, 16)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.83-84, p.186, pl.28)
